args:
The prince and his allies make for Clave
Loy'elune—the greatest of the Binding Ruins—
in an effort to find the secret of the Other said
to be sleeping within. When they arrive, they
steel themselves to delve into the depths of
the place, which is overflowing with miasma.
I shall return to life as one.
I shall return pure and whole!
Were you resting, Empress?\nThat is unusual for you.
Better you say I was rejoicing.
Pray forgive this fool's mistake, Empress.\nAnd to what happy incident do we owe\nthe blessing of your delight this day?
The pitiful Auspex, ever insistent on her\n＂resistance,＂ has reached her limit.
Because of this, my true body now comes\nforth, undulating and squirming furiously\nfrom the gate.
I fear the depth of your great words\nis lost upon this humble servant.
However, your joy is my own, Empress,\nand I am delighted to hear of it.
I am weary of your sycophantic buffoonery,\nHarle. Busy yourself instead with\npreparations for my departure.
Er, to where are you departing, Empress?
That question hardly bears asking.\nI make for the place where my body\nyet slumbers.
The resting spot of the fallen king's\nfleeting dream. Heh heh heh...
Leif escaped from the capital and has given\nus information about Clave Loy'elune. It's the\nplace where the secret of the Other sleeps.
On a solitary island south of Saint Lotier,\nan ancient ruin rests and waits.
What could be lying in wait there?\nAnd what IS the secret of the Other?
Whatever the truth may be, I'll overcome\nany hardship in order to save Zethia!
Watch yourself! This is no ordinary mist!
It shall prove a challenge to even\ndraw near to so much miasma.
We should avoid contacting it at all costs.\nThere is no telling what sort of effect\nit could have on the body.
Probably burn our whole faces clean off\nor melt us into little goo puddles, yeah?
I have no business with something\nthat would harm my perfect skin!

I figured this place would have traps
or whatnot since a secret of the Other
is here, but this is a bit more'n I was
bargainin' for.
It appears Clave Loy'elune will be a more\ntroublesome journey than we anticipated.
Clave Loy'elune...\nIt's been a long time...

There must be a reason a gloomy goose
like you came along, since that almost
never happens. Is there something here
you're specifically curious about?
This is a nostalgic place for me,\nand yet one filled with remorse.\nA place of determination and despair.
Might you please try to get to the point\njust a teeensy bit faster, mmm?
You do not understand. You, who sat upon\nthe volcano and saw the king off—
What?! How dare you! I'll have your hide\nfor that snide remark, dragon!
Zodiark, what exactly do you know\nabout Clave Loy'elune?
As you are well aware, Binding Ruins\nare scattered across Alberia.
And greatest among their number is this\nfell place—Clave Loy'elune.
Binding Ruins are where that thing that\npossessed Zethia was sealed away...
And of all those ruins, this one is\nthe greatest.
Think that's why there's so much miasma\nfloatin' around?
I got a bad feelin' about all this.
Which is precisely why we cannot\nclose our eyes to this threat.
On top of that, we might find a way\nto save Zethia here; we can't afford\nto shrink from that challenge.
Soonest begun, soonest done, I guess.\nInto Clave Loy'elune we go!
(Where it all ended...and where it\nall began.)
